Here's a complete implementation for swapping 1 ETH to USDC using the MetaMask Smart Accounts Kit with a delegation to authorize the swap.

## Setup

```typescript
import {
  Implementation,
  toMetaMaskSmartAccount,
  createDelegation,
  createExecution,
  ExecutionMode,
} from '@metamask/smart-accounts-kit'
import { DelegationManager } from '@metamask/smart-accounts-kit/contracts'
import {
  createPublicClient,
  createWalletClient,
  http,
  encodeFunctionData,
  parseEther,
  parseUnits,
} from 'viem'
import { sepolia } from 'viem/chains'
import { privateKeyToAccount } from 'viem/accounts'
import { createBundlerClient } from 'viem/account-abstraction'

const SWAP_CONTRACT = '0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000001'
const USDC_ADDRESS = '0x1c7D4B196Cb0C7B01d743Fbc6116a902379C7238' // Sepolia USDC
const SWAP_AMOUNT = parseEther('1') // 1 ETH

// Minimal swap ABI — adjust to match your contract's actual interface
const swapAbi = [
  {
    name: 'swapExactETHForTokens',
    type: 'function',
    inputs: [
      { name: 'amountOutMin', type: 'uint256' },
      { name: 'tokenOut', type: 'address' },
      { name: 'recipient', type: 'address' },
      { name: 'deadline', type: 'uint256' },
    ],
    outputs: [{ name: 'amountOut', type: 'uint256' }],
  },
] as const
```

## Create Smart Account

```typescript
const ownerAccount = privateKeyToAccount(process.env.PRIVATE_KEY as `0x${string}`)

const publicClient = createPublicClient({
  chain: sepolia,
  transport: http(),
})

// The user's smart account (delegator — holds the ETH)
const smartAccount = await toMetaMaskSmartAccount({
  client: publicClient,
  implementation: Implementation.Hybrid,
  deployParams: [ownerAccount.address, [], [], []],
  deploySalt: '0x',
  signer: { account: ownerAccount },
})

console.log('Smart account address:', smartAccount.address)
```

## Create & Sign Swap Delegation

```typescript
const environment = smartAccount.environment
const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)
const deadline = now + 3600 // 1 hour

// Encode the swap calldata
const swapCalldata = encodeFunctionData({
  abi: swapAbi,
  functionName: 'swapExactETHForTokens',
  args: [
    parseUnits('1800', 6), // amountOutMin: 1800 USDC (slippage protection)
    USDC_ADDRESS,
    smartAccount.address,  // recipient: tokens return to the smart account
    BigInt(deadline),
  ],
})

// Delegate authority to call the swap contract with exactly 1 ETH
const delegation = createDelegation({
  to: smartAccount.address, // self-delegation: account redeems its own delegation
  from: smartAccount.address,
  environment,
  scope: {
    type: 'functionCall',
    targets: [SWAP_CONTRACT],
    selectors: ['swapExactETHForTokens(uint256,address,address,uint256)'],
    valueLte: { maxValue: SWAP_AMOUNT }, // allow sending exactly 1 ETH
  },
  caveats: [
    // Lock to this exact calldata — no parameter manipulation possible
    { type: 'exactCalldata', calldata: swapCalldata },
    // Time-bound: only valid for 1 hour
    { type: 'timestamp', afterThreshold: now, beforeThreshold: now + 3600 },
    // Single use only
    { type: 'limitedCalls', limit: 1 },
  ],
})

// Sign the delegation
const signature = await smartAccount.signDelegation({ delegation })
const signedDelegation = { ...delegation, signature }
```

## Execute the Swap

```typescript
const bundlerClient = createBundlerClient({
  client: publicClient,
  transport: http('https://your-bundler-rpc.com'), // e.g. Pimlico, Alchemy
  // paymaster: paymasterClient, // optional: sponsor gas fees
})

// Build the execution: call swap contract with 1 ETH
const execution = createExecution({
  target: SWAP_CONTRACT,
  value: SWAP_AMOUNT,
  callData: swapCalldata,
})

// Encode the redemption call
const redeemCalldata = DelegationManager.encode.redeemDelegations({
  delegations: [[signedDelegation]],
  modes: [ExecutionMode.SingleDefault],
  executions: [[execution]],
})

// Send as a UserOperation from the smart account
const userOpHash = await bundlerClient.sendUserOperation({
  account: smartAccount,
  calls: [
    {
      to: smartAccount.address,
      data: redeemCalldata,
      value: 0n, // value is forwarded inside the execution, not here
    },
  ],
})

console.log('UserOperation hash:', userOpHash)

// Wait for receipt
const receipt = await bundlerClient.waitForUserOperationReceipt({
  hash: userOpHash,
})

console.log('Swap transaction hash:', receipt.receipt.transactionHash)
```

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Reason |
|---|---|
| `exactCalldata` caveat | Prevents any modification to swap parameters (recipient, min amount, deadline) |
| `valueLte` in scope | Required in v0.3.0 — function call scope sends **no ETH** by default |
| `limitedCalls: 1` | Ensures the delegation can only be redeemed once |
| `timestamp` caveat | Delegation expires with the swap deadline — no lingering authority |
| `amountOutMin` | Always set slippage protection; adjust based on current price oracle |

## Important Notes

> **⚠️ Verify the swap ABI** — `0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000001` is a placeholder. Replace `swapAbi` and the function selector with the actual interface of your swap contract before deploying.

> **⚠️ Account must be deployed** — The smart account must be deployed on-chain before the delegation can be redeemed. The first `sendUserOperation` call will deploy it automatically if it's counterfactual.

> **💡 Skipping delegation** — For a direct swap without delegation, simply call `bundlerClient.sendUserOperation` with `calls: [{ to: SWAP_CONTRACT, value: SWAP_AMOUNT, data: swapCalldata }]` directly.

